<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori kutsetegevuse alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for professional activities of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitor on kutsetegevuses s&otilde;ltumatu ja erapooletu ning juhindub &uuml;ksnes seadusest, auditeerimiseeskirjast, kutse-eetika n&otilde;uetest ning audiitorkogu organite otsustest ja soovitustest. </eesti>
<inglise>An auditor shall be independent and impartial in the professional activities of auditor and shall operate solely pursuant to law, the auditing rules, the requirements of professional ethics, and the resolutions and recommendations of the bodies of the Board of Auditors. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutsesaladuse hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of professional secrets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Audiitor on kohustatud hoidma saladuses kutsetegevuse k&auml;igus teatavaks saanud andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An auditor shall maintain the confidentiality of information which has become known to the auditor in the course of the professional activities of the auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud kohustus kehtib ka p&auml;rast audiitori kutsetegevuse l&otilde;petamist ning laieneb kutsekomisjoni ja audiitorkogu juhatuse liikmele, audiitori abilisele, audiitor&uuml;hingu ja audiitorkogu t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ning muule isikule, kellele on audiitori kutsesaladus teatavaks saanud t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The obligation shall remain in force also after the termination of the professional activities of an auditor and shall extend to the members of the professional qualifications committee and the management board of the Board of Auditors, assistants of auditors, employees of firms of auditors and the Board of Auditors and to other persons to whom a professional secret of an auditor has become known in the performance of their duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kutsesaladuse rikkumiseks ei loeta andmete avaldamist: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Disclosure of information is deemed not to be a violation of professional secrecy if such information is disclosed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) audiitorkogu juhatusele audiitori kutse s&auml;ilitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to the management board of the Board of Auditors in order to retain the qualification of an auditor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) distsiplinaarmenetluses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the course of disciplinary proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kohtule kohtum&auml;&auml;ruse v&otilde;i -otsuse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to a court on the basis of a court ruling or court judgment; </inglise>
<eesti>4) eeluurimisasutusele seoses kriminaalmenetlusega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to a preliminary investigation authority in connection with a criminal proceeding; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Riigikontrollile tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) to the State Audit Office for the performance of its duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(29.01.2002 j&otilde;ust.04.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 21, 117) </eesti>
<inglise>(29.01.2002 entered into force 04.03.2002 - RT I 2002, 21, 117) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori tegevuspiirang </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on activities of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Audiitor ei v&otilde;i tegutseda valdkonnas, mis v&otilde;ib m&otilde;jutada tema erapooletust v&otilde;i on kokkusobimatu hea audiitortavaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An auditor shall not operate in an area of activity which may influence the auditor's impartiality or is incompatible with good auditing practice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Audiitor esitab audiitorkogu juhatusele taotluse seisukoha saamiseks tegevusvaldkonna vastavuse kohta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 1. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An auditor shall submit an application to the management board of the Board of Auditors in order to obtain an opinion concerning the compliance of an area of activity with subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Audiitorkogu juhatus vastab taotlusele &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The management board of the Board of Auditors shall respond to an application within one month. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori varaline vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Proprietary liability of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Audiitor ja audiitor&uuml;hing vastutavad kutsetegevusega s&uuml;&uuml;liselt kliendile v&otilde;i kolmandale isikule tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An auditor or a firm of auditors shall be liable for any damage wrongfully caused to a client or a third party by the professional activities of the auditor or the firm of auditors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mitme audiitori v&otilde;i audiitor&uuml;hingu poolt &uuml;hiselt s&uuml;&uuml;liselt kliendile v&otilde;i kolmandale isikule tekitatud kahju eest vastutavad nad solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Several auditors or firms of auditors shall be solidarily liable for any damage wrongfully caused to a client or a third party jointly by the auditors or firms of auditors. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud n&otilde;ude aegumist&auml;htaeg on viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The limitation period for the claims specified in this section is five years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori kutsetegevusega seotud dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents concerning professional activities of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitor ja audiitor&uuml;hing s&auml;ilitavad kutsetegevusega seotud dokumente seitse aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>Auditors and firms of auditors shall preserve the documents concerning the professional activities for seven years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori kutsekindlustus </eesti>
<inglise>Professional liability insurance of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 40 s&auml;testatud kahju h&uuml;vitamise tagamiseks on audiitor kohustatud kogu oma kutsetegevuse ajaks s&otilde;lmima kutsekindlustuslepingu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to ensure compensation for damage provided for in &sect; 40 of this Act, an auditor shall enter into a professional liability insurance contract for the whole time the auditor is engaged in the professional activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kindlustussumma alamm&auml;&auml;ra ja kutsekindlustuslepingu olulised tingimused kehtestab audiitorkogu juhatus. (3) Kindlustusandjal on tagasin&otilde;ude&otilde;igus audiitori vastu, kui kindlustush&uuml;vis on v&auml;lja makstud kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks, mis tekkis audiitori tahtliku &otilde;igusvastase teo tagaj&auml;rjel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The management board of the Board of Auditors shall establish the minimum amount of indemnity and the essential terms and conditions of the professional liability insurance contract. (3) An insurer has the right of recourse against an auditor if an indemnity is paid to compensate for damage caused by an intentional unlawful act of the auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Kliendileping </eesti>
<inglise>Contracts with clients </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitor v&otilde;i audiitor&uuml;hing s&otilde;lmib kliendiga kirjaliku lepingu, kus m&auml;rgitakse lepingut t&auml;itev ning juhtivaudiitor, nende &uuml;lesanded, tasu vorm ja m&auml;&auml;r ning audiitori ja kliendi vastutus. </eesti>
<inglise>An auditor or a firm of auditors and a client shall enter into a written agreement which specifies the auditor who performs the contract and the auditor in charge, their obligations, the type and amount of their remuneration, and the liability of the auditor and the client. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori tegevuse j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision of activities of auditors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relevalvet audiitori tegevuse &uuml;le teostab audiitorkogu juhatus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervision over the activities of auditors shall be exercised by the management board of the Board of Auditors. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Audiitorkogu juhatusel on &otilde;igus kontrollida audiitori kutsetegevusega seotud dokumente ning saada audiitorilt kontrollimiseks vajalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The management board of the Board of Auditors has the right to examine documents relating to the professional activities of auditors and receive information from auditors necessary for the examination. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Audiitori distsiplinaarvastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary proceedings against auditors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse, audiitori tegevust reguleerivate muude &otilde;igusaktide, samuti audiitorkogu otsuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisel v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohasel t&auml;itmisel on audiitorkogu juhatusel &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta audiitor distsiplinaarvastutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an auditor fails to comply or complies inadequately with this Act, other legislation regulating the activities of auditors, or the resolutions of the Board of Auditors, the management board of the Board of Auditors has the right to bring disciplinary proceedings against the auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarkaristused on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Disciplinary punishments include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;rkus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) admonition; </inglise>
<eesti>2) noomitus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) reprimand; </inglise>
<eesti>3) rahatrahv; </eesti>
<inglise>3) fine; </inglise>
<eesti>4) audiitori kutsetegevuse peatamine kolmest kuust kuni &uuml;he aastani; </eesti>
<inglise>4) suspension of the professional activities of an auditor for a period of three months to one year; </inglise>
<eesti>5) audiitori kutsetegevuse l&otilde;petamine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) termination of the professional activities of an auditor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahatrahv ei v&otilde;i olla v&auml;iksem kui trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise ajal kehtinud Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;r ning suurem kui &uuml;ks kaheteistk&uuml;mnendik karistatava audiitori eelmise aasta sissetulek. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine shall not be less than the minimum monthly wage established by the Government of the Republic and applicable at the time the fine is imposed or more than one-twelfth of the income in the preceding year of the auditor who is punished. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahatrahv tasutakse audiitorkogule ja arvatakse audiitorkogu tuludesse. </eesti>
<inglise>A fine shall be paid to the Board of Auditors and shall be included in the income of the Board of Auditors. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Distsiplinaarasja menetlus, distsiplinaarkaristuse kohaldamise ja vaidlustamise kord s&auml;testatakse audiitorkogu p&otilde;hikirjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Disciplinary procedure and the procedure for the imposition and contestation of disciplinary punishments shall be provided for in the statutes of the Board of Auditors. </inglise>
